<br>
Once the slower tries to slow, I am never able to peel aggro back off with a windblade. I have to switch my sapper and hoh back in to get the job done. While tanking, I generally tend to use the sapper/hoh until the mob is at 80%. If I get a couple of procs, I'll switch before then. And if I proc my sapper before slow lands, I don't even have to worry about chasing down the mob, it stays with me.<br>
<br>
DPS does not equal aggro for warriors... our attack formulas are completely different than other classes. I have first hand experience with this. To test, I gave my ranger a Swiftblade of Zek and my Horn of Hsagra. Her DPS was way higher than mine. Now before you say rangers have all these nifty spells, she had no buffs (and was not casting spells) and neither did I. On the average I would say that she had ~20pts higher DPS than me.<br>
<br>
/shrug it seems pretty simple to me. Warriors rely on procs for aggro. Taunt isn't a reliable aggro getter, its best use is when the mobs turns away from you, to grab its attention back.<br>
<br>
That's my opinion, take it as you will. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://campus.pc.edu/students/bsawye00/kilamaalerdare.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78545"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Kilam Thorngage</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - 64 Warlord<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
